					<description><![CDATA[<p>Quaise Energy Raises $134 Million to Expand Superhot Geothermal Technology Quaise Energy raised $134 million to hasten the commercial development of its geothermal energy. Prelude Ventures led the funding round,</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/quaise-energy-raises-134-million-series-b/" data-wpel-link="internal">Quaise Energy Raises $134M Series B to Advance Superhot Geothermal Power</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Quaise Energy Raises $134 Million to Expand Superhot Geothermal Technology</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Quaise Energy raised $134 million to hasten the commercial development of its geothermal energy. Prelude Ventures led the funding round, with strategic investments from JERA and Idemitsu and participation by Safar Partners and others of its existing backers. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Quaise expects additional project equity and debt financing will be forthcoming in the year for its projects. The technology promises to tap previously accessible, but expensive, resources that the company aims to extract geothermal electricity from for the first time at utility scale.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founded in Houston, Quaise Energy aims to generate carbon-free, reliable electricity from wells with temperatures ranging from 400 to 1000 degrees </span><a href="https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/centigrade" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">centigrade</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> and from depths in excess of a mile below the Earth&#8217;s surface.</span></p>
<h2><b>Project Obsidian Moves Towards Commercial Deployment</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;Project Obsidian,&#8221; the company claims, will be the first commercial superhot geothermal power plant in the world. This could theoretically provide enough geothermal energy at competitive, renewable rates to power plants with the same sort of energy output as modern fossil fuels or nuclear plants.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Work on this facility is already ongoing at federally-owned geothermal leases in Oregon’s Deschutes National Forest. Project Obsidian is slated to start sending power to the grid in 2030 and will deliver firm baseload power, satisfying increasing demand for electricity in the Pacific Northwest.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In addition to its plans to move forward with Project Obsidian, Quaise is also going to continue work on its custom drilling rig, a &#8220;millimetre wave&#8221; system that uses the energy at very high frequencies to vaporise rock to reach 300C-500C heat at more than five miles underground.</span></p>
<h2><b>Field Testing Strengthens Commercial Confidence<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203398" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203398" class="size-full wp-image-203398" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/a-futuristic-neon-lit-poster-depicts-an-_BdjU1IsJWsGf1OgaRLvXAA_nX4r02OpSg2ZZdw0ksYOEA.png" alt="A neon futuristic visual showing advanced geothermal drilling technology reaching deep underground heat sources." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203398" class="wp-caption-text">Quaise advances superhot geothermal drilling technology as it pushes toward deeper, scalable clean energy production. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Quaise has spent more than a decade developing its drilling technology through research originating at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology. During 2025, the company successfully drilled more than 100 metres through granite at its Central Texas test site using its full-scale system.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company is now approaching one kilometre of drilling depth at the same location. According to Quaise, this would represent the deepest penetration achieved using millimetre wave drilling and the deepest recorded by any non-contact drilling technology.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Prelude Ventures has supported Quaise since its early stages. Managing Director Mark Cupta said the company&#8217;s recent field achievements demonstrate that superhot geothermal energy can become a practical large-scale energy source capable of supporting future electricity demand.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: <a href="https://ventureburn.com/tangos-raises-20-million-seed-funding/" data-wpel-link="internal">Tangos Raises $20 Million Seed Funding to Expand AI Financial Crime Investigations</a></span></p>
<h2><b>Demand Grows for Reliable Clean Energy</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Interest in geothermal energy has increased as countries seek dependable low-carbon electricity alongside solar and wind generation. Unlike intermittent renewable sources, geothermal power can generate electricity continuously regardless of weather conditions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Quaise believes its drilling technology dramatically expands the number of locations suitable for geothermal power generation. This could reduce dependence on fossil fuels while strengthening national energy independence.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The fresh capital will allow the company to continue commercialising its drilling technology while advancing Project Obsidian towards first revenue. Additional financing expected later this year will further support construction and project development.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As governments and energy companies accelerate investment in clean infrastructure, Quaise Energy is positioning superhot geothermal technology as a scalable source of reliable baseload electricity for future power systems.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/quaise-energy-raises-134-million-series-b/" data-wpel-link="internal">Quaise Energy Raises $134M Series B to Advance Superhot Geothermal Power</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
