					<description><![CDATA[<p>Tangos Raises $20 Million to Scale AI Investigation Platform Tangos has raised $20 million in seed funding to accelerate the development of its autonomous artificial intelligence platform for financial crime</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/tangos-raises-20-million-seed-funding/" data-wpel-link="internal">Tangos Raises $20 Million Seed Funding to Expand AI Financial Crime Investigations</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Tangos Raises $20 Million to Scale AI Investigation Platform</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Tangos has raised $20 million in seed funding to accelerate the development of its autonomous artificial intelligence platform for financial crime investigations. The round was led by Red Dot Capital Partners. It was founded in 2025 by serial entrepreneur Eyal Azoulay.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Leaders Fund, Clarim, Venture Israel, SignalFire, Clutch Capital, Selah Ventures and Bright Data also participated. Tangos develops AI technology that helps financial institutions investigate suspicious transactions, sanctions breaches and fraud cases. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The investment will support product development, customer expansion and research as demand for automated compliance tools grow. Tangos believes existing compliance teams cannot investigate every alert because of increasing workloads and a shortage of experienced investigators.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Senior executives include former officials from the United States Treasury&#8217;s Office of Foreign Assets Control and experienced AI infrastructure specialists. Financial crime generates more than $1.5 trillion in illicit proceeds every year. </span></p>
<h2><b>AI Focuses on Investigations Rather Than Detection</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Most compliance software identifies suspicious activity before handing cases to human investigators. The platform collates evidence, tests and validates a number of hypotheses and provides full, audit-ready investigation reports. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform can examine suspected transaction activities, investigate sanctions and money laundering risk, examine ultimate beneficial ownership structures and determine any secret relationships between organisations or individuals.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Regulator-ready reports can be produced, with each finding traceable back to the initial source data. According to the company, this helps improve transparency while supporting regulatory compliance.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founder and chief executive officer Eyal Azoulay said financial crime has become a complex network problem that exceeds the capacity of traditional investigation processes. He believes autonomous AI can significantly improve speed, consistency and investigative quality.</span></p>
<h2><b>Financial Institutions Adopt Autonomous Compliance Tools<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203394" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203394" class="size-full wp-image-203394" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/a-futuristic-poster-showcases-a-complex-_hbSeLnsSXiWjImifyd2xmA_LT5IoLcrT5-JUqeGSUUQxg.png" alt="A neon futuristic visual showing AI-powered financial investigation systems improving compliance and handling large volumes of alerts." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203394" class="wp-caption-text">Tangos enables institutions to scale financial crime investigations using structured AI systems designed for efficiency and compliance. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Tangos says its platform is already supporting major financial institutions, intelligence organisations and government agencies conducting high-risk investigations. Customers use the technology to strengthen compliance while increasing investigative capacity.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company argues this approach addresses one of the largest operational bottlenecks facing compliance departments. Financial institutions have invested heavily in systems that detect suspicious behaviour, but investigating those alerts remains labour-intensive and expensive.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Rather than relying on open-ended AI reasoning, Tangos structures its platform around specialised AI components designed for specific investigative tasks. These components follow predefined investigative </span><a href="https://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/english/methodology" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">methodologies</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> created with financial crime experts.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: <a href="https://ventureburn.com/norm-ai-raises-120-million-series-c/" data-wpel-link="internal">Norm Ai Raises $120 Million Series C to Expand AI Legal Platform</a></span></p>
<h2><b>Compliance Technology Market Continues to Grow</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Financial crimes coupled with increasing sophistication of criminals drives increasing demand for financial crime technology solutions. Banks, governments and fintech organizations are therefore increasingly relying on AI tools to gain efficiencies.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Tangos aims to use the investment to accelerate research initiatives and the roll-out of its platform into other regulated sectors. The company has not disclosed hiring targets but plans to strengthen its capabilities as enterprise demand grows.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As artificial intelligence becomes more widely adopted across compliance operations, Tangos is positioning itself to automate one of the most time-consuming stages of financial crime prevention while keeping human investigators responsible for final decisions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/tangos-raises-20-million-seed-funding/" data-wpel-link="internal">Tangos Raises $20 Million Seed Funding to Expand AI Financial Crime Investigations</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
