		<category><![CDATA[Google]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Proxima Fusion]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[RWE]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=203383</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Europe has just recorded a major leap forward in the global clean energy race. Munich-based nuclear fusion startup Proxima Fusion secures €411m in a financing round on Tuesday. This new</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/proxima-fusion-secures-411m-funding-google-backing/" data-wpel-link="internal">Proxima Fusion Secures €411M From Google, RWE To Build Europe’s Commercial Fusion Champion</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Europe has just recorded a major leap forward in the global clean energy race. Munich-based nuclear fusion startup Proxima Fusion secures €411m in a </span><a href="https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20260707899566/en/Proxima-Fusion-Raises-%E2%82%AC411-Million-at-a-%E2%82%AC2.4B-Valuation-to-Build-Europes-Commercial-Fusion-Champion" rel="nofollow sponsored external noopener noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">financing round</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> on Tuesday. This new capital pushes the company steps closer to its grand mission.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding round backed by Google and RWE takes Proxima’s total market valuation to €2.4 billion. With this historic milestone, the German deep-tech startup cements its status. It is now the most well-funded commercial fusion company in Europe. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The landmark deal signals that the continent is ready to lead the next generation of clean electricity. The market is watching closely as public and private capital merge.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Proxima Fusion is Driving the Fusion Race in Europe</span></h2>
<div id="attachment_203385" style="width: 682px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203385" class="size-full wp-image-203385" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Proxima-Fusion.jpg" alt="The official corporate logo for Proxima Fusion, featuring a modern geometric emblem and clean typography." width="672" height="350" /><p id="caption-attachment-203385" class="wp-caption-text">Proxima Fusion Official Logo</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The latest Proxima Fusion €411M funding round shows that global investors are betting heavily on European deep tech. XTX Ventures and East X Ventures stepped up to lead this massive financing round. Investors are looking past short-term market volatility to fund deep tech. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The round also saw appearances of heavyweights like KfW Capital, SPRIND and Burda Principal Investments. Early believers including Plural, UVC Partners, and Balderton Capital also doubled down on their support of Proxima Fusion. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This diverse backing proves that Europe can scale breakthrough tech. It shows the region can build globally competitive giants right at home. The sheer size of this investment signals a massive shift in how the private sector views long-term clean energy infrastructure.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More News: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/even-realities-raises-150m-to-expand-privacy-first-smart-glasses/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Even Realities Raises $150M To Expand Privacy-First Smart Glasses</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Google and RWE Strategic Power Move</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Tech giant Alphabet’s Google and German utility titan RWE joined this round as key strategic partners. RWE alone injected €25 million directly into the startup. Google’s involvement highlights a growing trend among massive tech firms. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Tech companies urgently require vast amounts of electricity, with zero carbon emissions, to run their rapidly expanding AI data centers. The need for artificial intelligence is so great that there is a need for revolutionary upgrades to the grid.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Meanwhile, RWE brings deep, practical energy grid expertise to the table. Their combined involvement proves that commercial fusion is no longer just a distant science project. Major corporate players see it as a viable, near-future solution to the global power crisis.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More News: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/bespoke-labs-raises-40m-ai-agent-training/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Bespoke Labs Raises $40M To Train Reliable Agents</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Transforming Nuclear Sites Into Clean Energy Hubs</span></h2>
<div id="attachment_203386" style="width: 864px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203386" class="size-full wp-image-203386" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Stellaris-design.jpg" alt="A digital rendering of Proxima Fusion&apos;s advanced stellarator concept, showcasing its intricate, twisted magnetic coil design." width="854" height="531" /><p id="caption-attachment-203386" class="wp-caption-text">Stellarator Reactor Concept. Image Credit: Proxima Fusion</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Proxima Fusion and RWE also signed a new Memorandum of Understanding (MoU). The two companies will collaborate to build the world’s first commercial stellarator fusion power plant. They chose a highly symbolic location for this ambitious project. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Reusing this infrastructure saves billions in development costs and speeds up deployment. The plant will sit on the site of a former nuclear fission facility in Gundremmingen, Bavaria. This brilliant move breathes new life into old energy infrastructure. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It utilizes existing high-voltage grid connections and specialized regional talent. It provides a clear blueprint for how legacy nuclear sites can transition cleanly into the next generation of power generation. To accomplish its ambitious goals, Proxima Fusion will be based on a cutting-edge stellarator technology. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In contrast to conventional tokamaks, stellarator designs hold superheated plasma continuously by employing a more complicated magnetic field. By the 2030s Proxima intends to sell power to the European grid. Thanks to this new €411 million cash injection, that aggressive timeline looks closer than ever before. </span></p>
