		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Tue, 07 Jul 2026 06:54:12 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Startup]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Even Realities]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[pre-Series B]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[smart glasses]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[unicorn]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[wearables]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=203372</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>The race for the space on your face is officially heating up. Smart glasses startup Even Realities raises $150 million in a pre-Series B funding round to push it into</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/even-realities-raises-150m-to-expand-privacy-first-smart-glasses/" data-wpel-link="internal">Even Realities Raises $150M To Expand Privacy-First Smart Glasses</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The race for the space on your face is officially heating up. Smart glasses startup Even Realities raises $150 million in a </span><a href="https://techcrunch.com/2026/07/06/smart-glasses-maker-even-realities-hits-1b-valuation-with-150m-funding-led-by-meituan-tencent/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">pre-Series B</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> funding round to push it into unicorn territory with a $1 billion valuation. Leading the round are Chinese tech giants Meituan and Tencent. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Even Realities is taking the opposite approach to tech giants such as Meta and Snap, which are filling their frames with cameras. They are working on smart glasses without the cameras. The move is designed to address the privacy issues that have plagued the rest of the wearable technology space.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A Bold Counter-Bet on Pure Privacy</span></h2>
<div id="attachment_203376" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203376" class="size-large wp-image-203376" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Even-G2-1024x672.jpg" alt="The Even Realities G2 smart glasses resting inside their specialized protective case, which doubles as a portable wireless power bank" width="1024" height="672" /><p id="caption-attachment-203376" class="wp-caption-text">G2 Smart Glasses. Image Credit: Even Realities</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Today’s smart glasses have a more surveillance-like feel than any in history. They record all that you view which may lead to a lot of discomfort for individuals around you. All that’s changed with Even Realities.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Their flagship product, the Even G2 does not have any camera. The startup’s solution to the privacy crisis is to remove the camera itself. These glasses do not record video but rather use a heads-up display.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">They beam vital notifications and directions straight into your field of view. Nobody else can see the text. Bystanders never have to worry about people filming them. Even their voice translation features process text instantly rather than saving permanent audio recordings.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More News: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/bespoke-labs-raises-40m-ai-agent-training/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Bespoke Labs Raises $40M To Train Reliable Agents</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Inside the G2 and R1 Ring Tech</span></h2>
<div id="attachment_203375" style="width: 877px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203375" class="size-full wp-image-203375" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Even-Realities-R1-Ring.jpg" alt="The Even Realities R1 smart ring serves as a gesture-controlled touchpad for navigating the glasses and a continuous wellness tracker." width="867" height="518" /><p id="caption-attachment-203375" class="wp-caption-text">R1 Ring. Image Credit: Even Realities</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The custom hardware is where Even Realities truly stands out from the crowd. The $599 Even G2 glasses utilize a unique two-layer lens system. The first layer shows quick notifications. The second layer projects longer text maps and navigation cues. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Powering this is their proprietary Even HAO optical technology. It blends microchips, waveguides, and prescription lens support into a single sleek piece of glass. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To keep your hands free and interactions subtle, the glasses pair with the Even R1 smart ring. Users simply tap or swipe the ring’s touchpad to navigate menus. The ring also pulls double duty as a health tracker, monitoring your heart rate and sleep patterns.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More News: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/kling-ai-raises-2-8-billion-with-alibaba-backing/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Kling AI Raises $2.8 Billion Backed By Alibaba &amp; Tencent</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Silicon Pedigree and Explosive Global Growth</span></h2>
<div id="attachment_203374" style="width: 749px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203374" class="size-full wp-image-203374" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Will-Wang.jpeg" alt="Even Realities founder and CEO Will Wang showcases the discreet, camera-free design of the brand&apos;s premium smart glasses." width="739" height="415" /><p id="caption-attachment-203374" class="wp-caption-text">Will Wang Wearing Smart Glasses. Image Credit: LinkedIn</p></div>
<p><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/will-wang-80609159?originalSubdomain=hk" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400">Will Wang</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, a former Apple engineer working on the iPhone and Apple Watch, established the startup in 2023. You can clearly see the premium build of that high-end pedigree of hardware in Even Realitites&#8217; products. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Interestingly, the company is headquartered in Shenzhen but has no plans to sell its glasses in China. Rather, it’s aimed at Western buyers. Its largest market is the USA, accounting for over half of users, and it is the fastest growing market. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The strategy is proving to be very effective. With prescription lenses added to orders, the average order value for Even Realities has reached $1,000, and has already achieved 10,000 units sold. The company is already a very profitable one with a turnover of 40 to almost 400 people in a matter of time.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/aligned-raises-60m-series-b/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Aligned Closes $60M Series B to Solidify Position in B2B Sales</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Funding the Next Interface Paradigm</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This $150 million capital will fuel the development of their next-gen wearable platform. The company plans to scale global operations and integrate deeper artificial intelligence capabilities. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Right now, users love their “Conversate” AI assistant, which translates languages and explains technical terms in real-time. Investors believe that the AI revolution needs a brand-new hardware interface beyond the traditional smartphone. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">By focusing on an all-day, screen-less experience that keeps users present, Even Realities is proving you can build a multi-billion-dollar tech company while respecting human privacy.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/even-realities-raises-150m-to-expand-privacy-first-smart-glasses/" data-wpel-link="internal">Even Realities Raises $150M To Expand Privacy-First Smart Glasses</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
